1
00:00:01,650 --> 00:00:05,466
Starting in 1915

2
00:00:06,633 --> 00:00:10,016
Armenians came as migrants from Turkey

3
00:00:10,283 --> 00:00:13,916
They came from Turkey via Syria, and they were received here

4
00:00:14,700 --> 00:00:16,900
Dr. Patrick Jakhmashian

5
00:00:18,148 --> 00:00:22,164
In this place there was no church, only halls

6
00:00:23,154 --> 00:00:25,620
All the families settled here

7
00:00:27,396 --> 00:00:29,612
And they would eat and drink in this place

8
00:00:29,692 --> 00:00:34,502
After that they built a church in that area

9
00:00:34,628 --> 00:00:38,362
Not this church; the old church was over there

10
00:00:39,642 --> 00:00:46,225
And in 1969

11
00:00:47,356 --> 00:00:52,122
They demolished the old church and built the new church

12
00:00:53,315 --> 00:00:55,547
Our rites were held every Friday

13
00:00:56,098 --> 00:01:00,264
Armenian families would gather here and perform prayers

14
00:01:04,724 --> 00:01:10,960
Interviewer: Tell us more about the rites
that took place here in this spot.

15
00:01:11,752 --> 00:01:15,518
Certainly, on holidays we gathered here

16
00:01:16,102 --> 00:01:18,335
And on January 6 we also celebrated

17
00:01:19,398 --> 00:01:21,414
On the major and minor holidays

18
00:01:21,447 --> 00:01:28,397
And now the Great Fast lasts fifty days after a month

19
00:01:28,569 --> 00:01:31,673
These are our rites, and after this fasting our feast will come

20
00:01:36,744 --> 00:01:41,881
In Mosul, before, there were

21
00:01:42,198 --> 00:01:45,097
Around 450 or 500 families

22
00:01:46,254 --> 00:01:48,904
But now just one family or two

23
00:01:50,392 --> 00:01:55,192
We are waiting for associations and organizations to rebuild the church

24
00:01:56,299 --> 00:01:57,739
Is it reasonable for it to stay like this?

25
00:02:00,489 --> 00:02:07,889
Interviewer: What is the reason for the small number of Armenian families inside Mosul?

26
00:02:08,290 --> 00:02:10,822
They left; they migrated to Erbil and Duhok

27
00:02:13,505 --> 00:02:17,190
So no one remained here except two families

28
00:02:17,410 --> 00:02:20,610
Of course we are waiting for the church to be rebuilt so they can return

29
00:02:21,573 --> 00:02:24,489
So that families come back from Duhok and Erbil to here

30
00:02:27,108 --> 00:02:29,525
On that side there was a library

31
00:02:30,642 --> 00:02:33,758
People would sit and read there

32
00:02:34,340 --> 00:02:38,406
It had full volumes of books, but now it has been destroyed
